{{Infobox academic| | image = Halvor Heyerdahl Rasch.jpg }} '''Halvor Heyerdahl Rasch''' (8 January 1805 – 26 August 1883) was a Norwegian [[zoologist]] and educator.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://nbl.snl.no/Halvor_Rasch|title= Halvor Rasch|publisher = Norsk biografisk leksikon |author= Preben S. Ottesen |accessdate= January 1, 2017 }}</ref>
He was born at [[Eidsberg]] in [[Østfold]], Norway. Rasch studied botany and zoology at the [[University of Oslo |University of Christiania]] (now University of Oslo). <ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2007 |title=Rasch, Halvor Heyerdahl |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location= |url=http://www.snl.no/article.html?id=729997 }}{{dead link|date=October 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He was a professor of zoology and natural science at the [[University of Oslo]] from 1852 to 1874, having previously been a lector since 1847.<ref>{{cite book|last=Jæger|first=Henrik|author2=Anderssen, Otto|title=Illustreret norsk Literaturhistorie. Videnskabernes Literatur i det nittende Aarhundrede|publisher=Hjalmar Biglers forlag|location=Kristiania|year=1896|volume=4|pages=112|url=http://runeberg.org/ilnolihi/4/0114.html}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ssb.no/emner/historisk_statistikk/artikler/art-2000-10-18-01.html Rovdyrstatistikk 1846-2000. Ulvejakt, mot og svindel] - [[Statistics Norway]]</ref>
An avid hunter and sportsman, he published the book ''Jagten i Norge'' (1845) as well as works about livestock, oyster cultivation and [[beekeeping]]. He was among the founders of the ''Centralforeningen for Udbredelse af Legemsøvelser og Vaabenbrug'', a precursor to the [[Norwegian Olympic and Paralympic Committee and Confederation of Sports|Norwegian Confederation of Sports]], in 1861.<ref name=snl/>
Rasch was decorated as a Knight of the [[Royal Norwegian Order of St. Olav]] in 1863 and received the Silver Medal of the Société Impériale Zoologique d'Acclimatation at Paris in 1866.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://runeberg.org/ilnolihi/4/0114.html |title= Halvor Heyerdahl Rasch|publisher = Illustreret norsk literaturhistorie |author= Henrik Jæger, Otto Anderssen |date= 1896 |accessdate= January 1, 2017 }}</ref>
