{{Infobox museum | name = The Etches Collection | image = File:The Etches Collection building, Kimmeridge, Dorset.jpg | caption = View of the building housing The Etches Collection from the main road in Kimmeridge | established = 2016 | location = [[Kimmeridge]], [[Dorset]], [[United Kingdom]] | visitors = | founder = [[Steve Etches]] | architect = Kennedy O'Callagahan Architects<ref name="kocarchitects">{{cite web| url=https://www.kocarchitects.com/the-etches-collection | title=The Etches Collection, Museum of Jurassic Marine Life | publisher=Kennedy O'Callagahan Architects | accessdate=22 August 2017 }}</ref> | website = [http://theetchescollection.org/ theetchescollection.org] }}
[[File:The Etches Collection gallery, Kimmeridge, Dorset.jpg|thumb|View of the main gallery in The Etches Collection]] [[File:Steve Etches in workshop, The Etches Collection, Kimmeridge, Dorset.jpg|thumb|The founder [[Steve Etches]] in the workshop at The Etches Collection]]
'''The Etches Collection''' (formerly known as the '''Museum of Jurassic Marine Life'''<ref name="tripadvisor">{{cite web| url=https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/Attraction_Review-g1765616-d11676132-Reviews-The_Etches_Collection_Museum_of_Jurassic_Marine_Life-Kimmeridge_Dorset_England.html | title=The Etches Collection, Museum of Jurassic Marine Life | publisher=[[TripAdvisor]] | accessdate=22 August 2017 }}</ref>) is a [[fossil]] [[museum]] in the village of [[Kimmeridge]], [[Isle of Purbeck|Purbeck]], [[Dorset]], [[England]].<ref name="william2017">{{cite article| first=Matt | last=Williams | title=The Etches Collection, Kimmeridge, Dorset | journal=[[Museums Journal]] | publisher=[[Museums Association]] | location=UK | volume=117 | number=2 | pages=52–55 | date=February 2017 }}</ref> It is based on the lifetime collection of [[Steve Etches]] from the local area on the [[Jurassic Coast]], a [[World Heritage Site]], especially around [[Kimmeridge Bay]] and the [[Kimmeridge Ledges]].
The museum building was opened in 2016 at a cost of £5 million to house a collection of over 2,000 fossil specimens.<ref name="bbc">{{cite news| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-dorset-37716484 | title=New museum at Kimmeridge for Etches Collection of fossils | publisher=[[BBC]] | work=[[BBC News]] | location=UK | date=21 October 2016 | accessdate=22 August 2017 }}</ref> Steve Etches had been collecting for over 30 years prior to the museum opening, and in this time he has amassed an important collection of fossils that form the basis of the collection.<ref name="telegraph">{{cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/08/12/amateur-fossil-hunter-who-spent-30-years-amassing-2000-specimens/ | title=Amateur fossil hunter who spent 30 years amassing 2,000 specimens wins grant to build £5m Jurassic Coast museum | newspaper=[[Daily Telegraph]] | location=UK | first=Alice | last=Shaw | date=12 August 2016 | accessdate=22 August 2017 }}</ref> The collection includes examples of [[ammonite]] eggs.<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Etches | first1=Steve | author-link1=Steve Etches | last2=Clarke | first2=Jane | last3=Callomon | first3=John | date=October 2008 | title=Ammonite eggs and ammonitellae from the Kimmeridge Clay Formation (Upper Jurassic) of Dorset, England | journal=[[Lethaia]] | volume=42 | number=2 | pages=204–217 | doi=10.1111/j.1502-3931.2008.00133.x }}</ref> The museum is considered world-class.<ref name="guardian">{{cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2016/nov/04/fossil-hunting-jurassic-coast-steve-etches-new-museum-dorset | title=Fossil fever: exploring Dorset's Jurassic Coast with Steve Etches | newspaper=[[The Guardian]] | location=UK | date=4 November 2016 | accessdate=22 August 2017 }}</ref>
The museum uses [[social media]] such as [[Facebook]]<ref>{{Facebook|theetchescollectionkimmeridge}}.</ref> and [[Twitter]].<ref>{{Twitter}}.</ref>
